1. On nije mogao da se pomiri sa *gubitkom* njegovog brata. (He couldn't come to terms with the loss of his brother.)
2. *Gubitak* nekog voljenog člana porodice je težak teret. (The loss of a beloved family member is a heavy burden.)
3. On je zaplakao zbog *gubitka* njegovog omiljenog predmeta. (He cried over the loss of his favorite object.)
4. Učinio je sve što je mogao da smanji *gubitke*. (He did all he could to minimize the losses.)
5. *Gubitak* njegovog posla je bio za njega težak udarac. (The loss of his job was a hard blow for him.)